    "app_id": "A0AFMJ099PA",
    "text": "AI Agent vs. Agentic AI: Key Differences\n\n*AI Agent:* An AI agent is a software entity designed to perform a specific task or a small set of tasks on behalf of a user or system. It receives input, processes it using rules/models/logic, performs an action, and stops when the task is done. It's focused, scoped, and usually short-lived. They function within strict guidelines, processing inputs and responding based on preprogrammed rules.\n\n*Agentic AI:* Agentic AI is a system-level capability where AI exhibits agency. Agency means the ability to set/refine goals, plan multiple steps, take actions autonomously, monitor outcomes, and adapt behavior over time. Agentic AI systems often consist of multiple AI agents working together, guided by memory, reasoning loops, feedback mechanisms, and sometimes human oversight. It behaves less like a tool and more like a digital worker or digital organization.\n\nKey Differences:\n| Aspect | AI Agent | Agentic AI |\n|---|---|---|\n| Core Idea | Executes a specific task when instructed | Achieves goals autonomously using planning and reasoning |\n| Scope | Narrow and well-defined | Broad and flexible |\n| Autonomy Level | Low to moderate | High |\n| Behavior | Reactive | Proactive and adaptive |\n| Decision Making | Follows predefined instructions/prompts | Makes decisions based on goals and context |\n| Goal Setting | Goals are given by humans | Can refine or break down goals into sub-goals |\n| Planning Ability | Minimal or none | Strong multi-step planning |\n| Memory Usage | Little or no long-term memory | Uses short-term and long-term memory |\n| Feedback Loops | Rare or manual | Continuous self-evaluation and adjustment |\n| Number of Agents | Usually single agent | Often multiple agents working together |\n\nSources: <http://geeksforgeeks.org|geeksforgeeks.org>, <http://c-sharpcorner.com|c-sharpcorner.com>",
    "team": "T0AET1ZEYCA",
    "bot_profile": {
      "id": "B0AER7Q28DU",
      "app_id": "A0AFMJ099PA",
      "user_id": "U0AEBRSE03Z",
      "name": "Slack-Agent",
