    "text": "Summaries of research papers related to agentic AI security:\n\n*Security Analysis of Agentic Communication Protocols*\nThis paper presents the first empirical, comparative security analysis of the official CORAL implementation and a high-fidelity, SDK-based ACP implementation, benchmarked against a literature-based evaluation of A2A. Using a 14 point vulnerability taxonomy, the authors systematically assess their defenses across authentication, authorization, and other security aspects. It finds that the security of communication protocols in multi-agent systems is critically under-examined.\n\n*AI Agents vs. Agentic AI: A Conceptual taxonomy, applications and challenges*\nThis paper provides a conceptual taxonomy to differentiate between AI Agents and Agentic AI. It explores applications and challenges related to both types of AI, offering a framework for understanding the nuances and complexities of agentic AI in various contexts.\n\n*Generative Intrusion Detection and Prevention on Data Stream*\nThis paper likely focuses on using generative models for intrusion detection and prevention in data streams. It contributes to the field by proposing a novel approach for identifying and mitigating security threats in real-time data environments. However, without more context, a precise summary is difficult.",
